The paper deals with a graph partitioning problem, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of submodular functions and the application of classic results suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also involves cutting a graph, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.CC). Finally, the use of a branching scheme and time complexity analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of game theory (cs.GT).
